p: Compound 5 is a structural analogue of acetophenone, which had been previously determined to be highly active in terms of inducing sedation in mice [ 21]. Therefore, resemblances in their structure might explain the similar sedative effect observed in compound 5. Aside from agarwood, compound 5 is also a main volatile constituent of Propolis essential oil (collected from Albania), which is slowly becoming popular for its promising biological activities [ 38].
